<subSubSection id="C343656DFFF2FFDC09EEFAB5B3BEFEA0" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="190" pageId="2" pageNumber="189" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE636E6FFF2FFDC09EEFAB5B37FFE84" blockId="2.[151,1437,1513,2008]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,150,501]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="190" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF2FFDD09EEFAB5B35EF9C6" bold="true" box="[199,322,1513,1539]" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D65FFF2FFDD08F3FAB6B07DF9C6" authority="Huang &amp; Jiang &amp; Song, 2021" authorityName="Huang &amp; Jiang &amp; Song" authorityYear="2021" box="[474,609,1513,1539]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Teratozephyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yaolihuoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF2FFDD08F3FAB6B07DF9C6" box="[474,609,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">T. yaolihuoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF2FFDD0B41FAB6B0DFF9C1" bold="true" box="[616,707,1514,1540]" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21E578FFFF2FFDD0B41FAB6B0DFF9C1" box="[616,707,1514,1540]" pageId="2" pageNumber="189" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
externally resembles only 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D65FFF2FFDD0ADDFAB6B73EF9C1" authority="Fujioka, 1994" authorityName="Fujioka" authorityYear="1994" box="[1012,1314,1513,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Teratozephyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hinomaru">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF2FFDD0ADDFAB6B662F9C6" box="[1012,1150,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">T. hinomaru</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC84B17FFF2FFDD0DACFAB5B73EF9C1" author="Fujioka, T." box="[1157,1314,1513,1540]" journalOrPublisher="Butterflies" pageId="2" pageNumber="189" pagination="44 - 55" part="8" refId="ref3076" refString="Fujioka, T. (1994) Zephyrus (Theclini butterflies) in the world (6) - genera Teratozephyrus and Esakiozephyrus. Butterflies, 8, 44 - 55. [in Japanese]" title="Zephyrus (Theclini butterflies) in the world (6) - genera Teratozephyrus and Esakiozephyrus" type="journal article" year="1994">Fujioka, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13622A63FFF2FFDD0C1BFAB5B78BF9C1" box="[1330,1431,1513,1540]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1407,1431]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,1384]" captionTargetId="figure-122@2.[151,1435,381,1384]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Teratozephyrus spp. adults. 1, T. yaolihuoi sp. nov., holotype male, SE. China, Fujian (CFJ); 2, ditto, underside; 3, T. hinomaru, male, SW. China, Guizhou, TSY001 (CHSY); 4, ditto, underside. Scale=1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4711140" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4711140/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">Figs 3–4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13622A63FFF2FFDD09BEF951B2BBF9E2" box="[151,167,1549,1575]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1746,1770]" captionTargetBox="[163,1429,528,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-152@3.[151,1436,525,1722]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Male genitalia of Teratozephyrus spp. 5, T. yaolihuoi sp. nov., holotype, dissection number JF200; 6, T. hinomaru, dissection number TSY001. a=genitalia capsule with aedeagus removed, in left lateral view; b= ditto, in right lateral view; c= ditto, in ventral view; d=ditto, in dorsal view; e=valvae and juxta, in ventral view; f=ditto, in dorsal view; g= ditto, in ventroposterior view; h=right branch of gnathos (falx), in lateral view; i= ditto, in dorsal view; j=phallus in dorsal view; k=phallus in lateral view, in pale background, showing the sclerotized parts; l= ditto, in grey background, showing the membranous parts. LP=lateral process; LW=lateral window; jx=juxta. Scale=1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4711142" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4711142/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13622A63FFF2FFDD099FF952B2FFF9ED" box="[182,227,1550,1576]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,664,688]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,181,640]" captionTargetId="figure-25@4.[151,1435,181,640]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–8. Holotype of Teratozephyrus hinomaru from Fujioka (1994). 7, male adult, a=upperside; b=underside; 8, male genitalia. a=uncus and socii in dorsal view; b=genitalia capsule in right lateral view with valvae and aedeagus removed; c=valvae in right lateral view; d=phallus in right lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4711144" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4711144/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">7–8</figureCitation>
, 
<typeStatus id="54E28844FFF2FFDD09DBF952B33EF9ED" box="[242,290,1550,1576]" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">type</typeStatus>
locality: Chin-fo-shan, Nanchuan, Szechuan, now Mt. Jinfou, Nanchuan District, 
<collectingRegion id="499DF804FFF2FFDD0DF5F951B744F9E2" box="[1244,1368,1549,1575]" country="China" name="Chongqing" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">Chongqing</collectingRegion>
City) from 
<collectingRegion id="499DF804FFF2FFDD09FFF96DB34EF98E" box="[214,338,1585,1611]" country="China" name="Chongqing" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">Chongqing</collectingRegion>
City and 
<collectingRegion id="499DF804FFF2FFDD08EAF96DB08DF98E" box="[451,657,1585,1611]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">Guizhou Province</collectingRegion>
, southwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F34E7676FFF2FFDD0A10F96DB160F98E" box="[825,892,1585,1611]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">China</collectingCountry>
in sharing a similar intense orange patch on the forewing upperside, The new species, however, can be readily distinguished from the latter externally by the following features: 1) on the upperside of the forewing, the orange patch is less extensive and not extending to space 
<quantity id="4CA19B03FFF2FFDD09BEF9C1B2D8F972" box="[151,196,1693,1719]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.524" pageId="2" pageNumber="189" unit="in" value="6.0">6 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C594D65FFF2FFDD09E4F9C1B32BF972" authorityName="Huang &amp; Jiang &amp; Song" authorityYear="2021" box="[205,311,1693,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Teratozephyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yaolihuoi">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF2FFDD09E4F9C1B32BF972" box="[205,311,1693,1719]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">yaolihuoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while that in 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D65FFF2FFDD08F6F9C2B076F972" authorityName="Fujioka" authorityYear="1994" box="[479,618,1693,1719]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Teratozephyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hinomaru">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF2FFDD08F6F9C2B076F972" box="[479,618,1693,1719]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">T. hinomaru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is much larger and forming a long orange bar in the space 6; 2) on the underside of both wings, the ground color is yellowish brown without a reddish tint in the new species, while the ground color is ochreous brown with a reddish tint in 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D65FFF2FFDD0BD5F9BAB199F93A" authorityName="Fujioka" authorityYear="1994" box="[764,901,1765,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Teratozephyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hinomaru">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF2FFDD0BD5F9BAB199F93A" box="[764,901,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">T. hinomaru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D65FFF2FFDD0D4BF9BAB6F4F93A" authority="Huang &amp; Jiang &amp; Song, 2021" authorityName="Huang &amp; Jiang &amp; Song" authorityYear="2021" box="[1122,1256,1765,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Teratozephyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yaolihuoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF2FFDD0D4BF9BAB6F4F93A" box="[1122,1256,1765,1791]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">T. yaolihuoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF2FFDD0DD9F9BAB757F8C5" bold="true" box="[1264,1355,1766,1792]" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21E578FFFF2FFDD0DD9F9BAB757F8C5" box="[1264,1355,1766,1792]" pageId="2" pageNumber="189" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D65FFF2FFDD0846F856B3EBF8E6" authorityName="Fujioka" authorityYear="1994" box="[367,503,1801,1827]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Teratozephyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hinomaru">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF2FFDD0846F856B3EBF8E6" box="[367,503,1801,1827]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">T. hinomaru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
soundly by the following characters: 1) uncus is significantly narrowing towards its tip in the dorsal view, while that in 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D65FFF2FFDD0B08F872B0B5F882" authorityName="Fujioka" authorityYear="1994" box="[545,681,1837,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Teratozephyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hinomaru">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF2FFDD0B08F872B0B5F882" box="[545,681,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">T. hinomaru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is much broader throughout the whole length and only slightly narrowing at the distal end; 2) uncus, in the lateral view, is not broadening towards the base, while that in 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D65FFF2FFDD0C3DF80EB780F8AE" authorityName="Fujioka" authorityYear="1994" box="[1300,1436,1873,1899]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Teratozephyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hinomaru">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF2FFDD0C3DF80EB780F8AE" box="[1300,1436,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">T. hinomaru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is significantly broadening towards the base; 3) tegumen, in the dorsal view, is wide with the horizontal width much longer than the length of the uncus, while tegumen in the dorsal view is narrower with the horizontal width slightly longer than the length of the uncus 
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF2FFDD0B05F8E2B0C8F812" box="[556,724,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D65FFF2FFDD0B63F8E2B0C8F812" authorityName="Fujioka" authorityYear="1994" box="[586,724,1981,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Teratozephyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hinomaru">T. hinomaru</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
; 4) branch of gnathos (falx) in lateral view is curving near the distal end, while that in 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D65FFF3FFDC088EFFCBB02CFF74" authorityName="Fujioka" authorityYear="1994" box="[423,560,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Teratozephyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hinomaru">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF3FFDC088EFFCBB02CFF74" box="[423,560,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">T. hinomaru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is curving slightly before the middle point of the whole length; 5) sacculus is rounded in ventro-posterior view, while that in 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D65FFF3FFDC0B9FFFE7B15CFF10" authorityName="Fujioka" authorityYear="1994" box="[694,832,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Teratozephyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hinomaru">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF3FFDC0B9FFFE7B15CFF10" box="[694,832,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">T. hinomaru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sharper and forming a triangular projection in the same view; 6) aedeagus has its distal end slightly bending downwards, and aedeagus vesica has shorter cornuti at its base, while the distal end of aedeagus in 
<taxonomicName id="4C594D65FFF3FFDC0BABFE5FB116FED8" authorityName="Fujioka" authorityYear="1994" box="[642,778,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Teratozephyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hinomaru">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF3FFDC0BABFE5FB116FED8" box="[642,778,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">T. hinomaru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is pointing forwards and aedeagus vesica has much longer cornuti at its base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE636E6FFF3FFDC09EEFE17B3BEFEA0" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,501]" box="[199,418,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF3FFDC09EEFE17B339FEA0" bold="true" box="[199,293,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C343656DFFF3FFDC09EEFE32B734FE4C" box="[199,1320,366,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE636E6FFF3FFDC09EEFE32B734FE4C" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,501]" box="[199,1320,366,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF3FFDC09EEFE32B37DFE4D" bold="true" box="[199,353,366,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Distribution.</emphasis>
Currently only known from the 
<typeStatus id="54E28844FFF3FFDC0BE5FE33B0E0FE4C" box="[716,764,367,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">type</typeStatus>
locality in northwestern 
<collectingRegion id="499DF804FFF3FFDC0D3CFE33B6DBFE4C" box="[1045,1223,367,393]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fujian Province</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="13622A63FFF3FFDC0DFFFE33B706FE4C" box="[1238,1306,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1493,1517]" captionTargetBox="[151,1428,784,1458]" captionTargetId="figure-72@4.[151,1436,784,1469]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9. Distribution map of Teratozephyrus spp. mentioned in the current study." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4711146" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4711146/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C343656DFFF3FFDC09EEFECFB34DFE30" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE636E6FFF3FFDC09EEFECFB34DFE30" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis id="B92DEAF4FFF3FFDC09EEFECFB352FE68" bold="true" box="[199,334,403,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is dedicated to the memory of Mr. Li-Huo Yao, a butterfly amateur who collected the 
<typeStatus id="54E28844FFF3FFDC09BEFEEBB2E5FE14" box="[151,249,439,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">holotype</typeStatus>
of this interesting lycaenid butterfly and devoted most of his life to investigating the butterfly fauna of 
<collectingRegion id="499DF804FFF3FFDC09BEFE87B351FE30" box="[151,333,475,501]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="3" pageNumber="190">Fujian Province</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
